                                    <watches>0</watches>
                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13206268" author="markrmiller@gmail.com" created="Sat, 11 Feb 2012 21:08:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;For the moment I&apos;ve just remove the interrupt that was being used - future improvements can be made around stopping replication mid stream - nothing we can do about sleeps easily, but that is not a big deal. We have timeouts for http connections, so that shouldn&apos;t be too terrible either.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13208063" author="markrmiller@gmail.com" created="Tue, 14 Feb 2012 22:01:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Since we no longer interrupted, zk retry operations could retry for a long time, even if recovery was cancelled - so I&apos;ve worked around this (SafeStopThread interface) and just committed a fix.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
